<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-08-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-08-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="24" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d24">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 363.117/8</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 318.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-08-26">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 26, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your despatch
                            No. 514, of August 4, 1913, transmitting a copy of your note of August
                            2nd to the Austro-Hungarian Foreign Office protesting against
                            unwarranted arrests of naturalized American citizens in
                            Austria-Hungary.</p>
                        <p>The Department approves of your note and hopes that it may have the
                            desired effect.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">J. B. Moore</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>